%N A393951 Decimal expansion of Sum_{p prime, k>=0} 1/(p^(2^(k+1)) + 2*p^(2^k)) * Product_{p prime} ((1-1/p)^2 * Product_{k>=0} (1 + 2/p^(2^k))).
%C A393951 The asymptotic probability that the greatest common infinitary divisor of two positive integers selected independently at random is a "Fermi-Dirac prime" (A050376).
%F A393951 Equals Sum_{p prime, k>=0} 1/(p^(2^(k+1)) + 2*p^(2^k)) * A393948.
%e A393951 0.235439084951993028533217989556236772680136440488478...
%o A393951 (PARI) c(m) = sumeulerrat(sum(k = 0, m, 1/(p^(2^(k+1)) + 2*p^(2^k)))) * prodeulerrat((1 - 1/p)^2 * prod(k = 0, m, 1 + 2/p^(2^k)));
%o A393951 {my(c1 = 0, c2 = 1, m = 1); while(c2 != c1, c1 = c2; c2 = c(m); m++); c2}
%Y A393951 Cf. A050376, A077609.
%Y A393951 The asymptotic probability that the greatest common infinitary divisor of two positive integers selected independently at random is: A065472 (square), A393948 (1), A393949 (prime), A393950 (squarefree), this constant (Fermi-Dirac prime), A393952 (exponentially 2^n-number), A393953 (4th power).
%K A393951 nonn,cons
%O A393951 0,1
